name: Bulbasaur
description: The Seed Pokémon. It can go for days without eating a single morsel. In the bulb on its back, it stores energy.

name: Ivysaur
description: The Seed Pokémon. The bud on its back grows by drawing energy. It gives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.

name: Venusaur
description: The Seed Pokémon. The flower on its back catches the sun’s rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy

name: Charmander
description: The Lizard Pokémon. The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as it burns. You can only hear it in quiet places.

name: Charmeleon
description: The Flame Pokémon. Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When excited, it may breathe out bluish-white flames.

name: Charizard
description: The Flame Pokémon. When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

name: Squirtle
description: The Tiny Turtle Pokémon. Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

name: Wartortle
description: The Turtle Pokémon. When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull it in, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

name: Blastoise
description: The Shellfish Pokémon. Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.

name: Caterpie
description: The Worm Pokémon. If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will release a horrible stink to protect itself.

name: Metapod
description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Hardens its shell to protect itself. However, a large impact may cause it to pop out of its shell.

name: Butterfree
description: The Butterfly Pokémon. Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.

name: Weedle
description: The Hairy Bug Pokémon. Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

name: Kakuna
description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

name: Beedrill
description: The Poison Bee Pokémon. It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

name: Pidgey
description: The Tiny Bird Pokémon. Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

name: Pidgeotto
description: The Bird Pokémon. This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

name: Pidgeot
description: The Bird Pokémon. This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

name: Rattata
description: The Mouse Pokémon. Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

name: Raticate
description: The Mouse Pokémon. Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

name: Spearow
description: The Tiny Bird Pokémon. Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

name: Fearow
description: The Beak Pokémon. A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

name: Ekans
description: The Snake Pokémon. The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

name: Arbok
description: The Cobra Pokémon. The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

name: Pikachu
description: The Mouse Pokémon. This forest-dwelling Pokémon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you’ll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.

name: Raichu
description: The Mouse Pokémon. When electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.

name: Sandshrew
description: The Mouse Pokémon. Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its hide is said to become coated with a fine dew.

name: Sandslash
description: The Mouse Pokémon. It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws. If broken, they start to grow back in a day.

name: Nidoran ♀
description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.

name: Nidorina
description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

name: Nidoqueen
description: The Drill Pokémon. Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

name: Nidoran ♂
description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

name: Nidorino
description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

name: Nidoking
description: The Drill Pokémon. Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

name: Clefairy
description: The Fairy Pokémon. Adored for their cute looks and playfulness. They are thought to be rare, as they do not appear often.

name: Clefable
description: The Fairy Pokémon. They appear to be very protective of their own world. It is a kind of fairy, rarely seen by people.

name: Vulpix
description: The Fox Pokémon. Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

name: Ninetales
description: The Fox Pokémon. According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

name: Jigglypuff
description: The Balloon Pokémon. Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff
description: The Balloon Pokémon. Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

name: Zubat
description: The Bat Pokémon. Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

name: Golbat
description: The Bat Pokémon. It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

name: Oddish
description: The Weed Pokémon. It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

name: Gloom
description: The Weed Pokémon. Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

name: Vileplume
description: The Flower Pokémon. Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

name: Paras
description: The Mushroom Pokémon. Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

name: Parasect
description: The Mushroom Pokémon. The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

name: Venonat
description: The Insect Pokémon. Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

name: Venomoth
description: The Poison Moth Pokémon. The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

name: Diglett
description: The Mole Pokémon. It prefers dark places. It spends most of its time underground, though it may pop up in caves.

name: Dugtrio
description: The Mole Pokémon. A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth of 60 miles. It’s reported that this triggers an earthquake.

name: Meowth
description: The Scratch Cat Pokémon. Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can’t stop itself from picking them up.

name: Persian
description: The Classy Cat Pokémon. The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.

name: Psyduck
description: The Duck Pokémon. Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but whether it intends to do so is not known.

name: Golduck
description: The Duck Pokémon. Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

name: Mankey
description: The Pig Monkey Pokémon. An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

name: Primeape
description: The Pig Monkey Pokémon. It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

name: Growlithe
description: The Puppy Pokémon. A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

name: Arcanine
description: The Legendary Pokémon. A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

name: Poliwag
description: The Tadpole Pokémon. The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

name: Poliwhirl
description: The Tadpole Pokémon. Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

name: Poliwrath
description: The Tadpole Pokémon. Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

name: Abra
description: The Psi Pokémon. Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

name: Kadabra
description: The Psi Pokémon. Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.

name: Alakazam
description: The Psi Pokémon. A Pokémon that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns—that’s why this Pokémon is smart.

name: Machop
description: The Superpower Pokémon. Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.

name: Machoke
description: The Superpower Pokémon. The belt around its waist holds back its energy. Without it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.

name: Machamp
description: The Superpower Pokémon. One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this Pokémon fires off awesome punches.

name: Bellsprout
description: The Flower Pokémon. Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

name: Weepinbell
description: The Flycatcher Pokémon. When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

name: Victreebel
description: The Flycatcher Pokémon. Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

name: Tentacool
description: The Jellyfish Pokémon. It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

name: Tentacruel
description: The Jellyfish Pokémon. Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

name: Geodude
description: The Rock Pokémon. Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

name: Graveler
description: The Rock Pokémon. Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

name: Golem
description: The Megaton Pokémon. Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

name: Ponyta
description: The Fire Horse Pokémon. Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.

name: Rapidash
description: The Fire Horse Pokémon. Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

name: Slowpoke
description: The Dopey Pokémon. Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.

name: Slowbro
description: The Hermit Crab Pokémon. Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

name: Magnemite
description: The Magnet Pokémon. It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.

name: Magneton
description: The Magnet Pokémon. Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.

name: Farfetch'd
description: The Wild Duck Pokémon. They live where reedy plants grow. Farfetch’d are rarely seen, so it’s thought their numbers are decreasing.

name: Doduo
description: The Twin Bird Pokémon. Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

name: Dodrio
description: The Triple Bird Pokémon. One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

name: Seel
description: The Sea Lion Pokémon. Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Dewgong
description: The Sea Lion Pokémon. Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

name: Grimer
description: The Sludge Pokémon. Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

name: Muk
description: The Sludge Pokémon. Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

name: Shellder
description: The Bivalve Pokémon. The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.

name: Cloyster
description: The Bivalve Pokémon. For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamond shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.

name: Gastly
description: The Gas Pokémon. Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape, as it appears to be made of a gas.

name: Haunter
description: The Gas Pokémon. By licking, it saps the victim’s life. It causes shaking that won’t stop until the victim’s demise.

name: Gengar
description: The Shadow Pokémon. A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.

name: Onix
description: The Rock Snake Pokémon. Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

name: Drowzee
description: The Hypnosis Pokémon. If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

name: Hypno
description: The Hypnosis Pokémon. Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

name: Krabby
description: The River Crab Pokémon. Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

name: Kingler
description: The Pincer Pokémon. One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

name: Voltorb
description: The Ball Pokémon. It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

name: Electrode
description: The Ball Pokémon. Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

name: Exeggcute
description: The Egg Pokémon. The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

name: Exeggutor
description: The Coconut Pokémon. Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.

name: Cubone
description: The Lonely Pokémon. Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.

name: Marowak
description: The Bone Keeper Pokémon. Small and weak, this Pokémon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.

name: Hitmonlee
description: The Kicking Pokémon. When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.

name: Hitmonchan
description: The Punching Pokémon. Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.

name: Lickitung
description: The Licking Pokémon. Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.

name: Koffing
description: The Poison Gas Pokémon. In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!

name: Weezing
description: The Poison Gas Pokémon. This Pokémon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.

name: Rhyhorn
description: The Spikes Pokémon. A Pokémon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won’t stop running until it falls asleep.

name: Rhydon
description: The Drill Pokémon. Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

name: Chansey
description: The Egg Pokémon. A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.

name: Tangela
description: The Vine Pokémon. Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

name: Kangaskhan
description: The Parent Pokémon. Raises its young in its belly pouch. Won’t run from any fight to keep its young protected.

name: Horsea
description: The Dragon Pokémon. If it senses any danger, it will vigorously spray water or a special type of ink from its mouth.

name: Seadra
description: The Dragon Pokémon. Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

name: Goldeen
description: The Goldfish Pokémon. When it is time for them to lay eggs, they can be seen swimming up rivers and falls in large groups.

name: Seaking
description: The Goldfish Pokémon. It is the male’s job to make a nest by carving out boulders in a stream using the horn on its head.

name: Staryu
description: The Star Shape Pokémon. As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pokémon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

name: Starmie
description: The Mysterious Pokémon. The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in seven colors.

name: Mr. Mime
description: The Barrier Pokémon. Always practicing its pantomime act. It makes enemies believe something exists that really doesn’t.

name: Scyther
description: The Mantis Pokémon. Leaps out of tall grass and slices prey with its scythes. The movement looks like that of a ninja.

name: Jynx
description: The Human Shape Pokémon. Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

name: Electabuzz
description: The Electric Pokémon. If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

name: Magmar
description: The Spitfire Pokémon. Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

name: Pinsir
description: The Stag Beetle Pokémon. Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can’t move if it’s cold out, so it lives in warm places.

name: Tauros
description: The Wild Bull Pokémon. A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won’t stop until it hits something.

name: Magikarp
description: The Fish Pokémon. Famous for being very unreliable. It can be found swimming in seas, lakes, rivers, and shallow puddles.

name: Gyarados
description: The Atrocious Pokémon. Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

name: Lapras
description: The Transport Pokémon. A gentle soul that can understand human speech. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.

name: Ditto
description: The Transform Pokémon. When it spots an enemy, its body transfigures into an almost-perfect copy of its opponent.

name: Eevee
description: The Evolution Pokémon. Eevee’s genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

name: Vaporeon
description: The Bubble Jet Pokémon. Its cell structure is similar to water molecules. It melts into the water and becomes invisible.

name: Jolteon
description: The Lightning Pokémon. A sensitive Pokémon that easily becomes sad or angry. Every time its mood changes, it charges power.

name: Flareon
description: The Flame Pokémon. It has a flame chamber inside its body. It inhales, then breathes out fire that is over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
description: The Virtual Pokémon. The only Pokémon that people anticipate can fly into space. None has managed the feat yet, however.

name: Omanyte
description: The Spiral Pokémon. An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

name: Omastar
description: The Spiral Pokémon. Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

name: Kabuto
description: The Shellfish Pokémon. A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

name: Kabutops
description: The Shellfish Pokémon. A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

name: Aerodactyl
description: The Fossil Pokémon. A savage Pokémon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

name: Snorlax
description: The Sleeping Pokémon. Will eat anything, even if the food happens to be a little moldy. It never gets an upset stomach.

name: Articuno
description: The Freeze Pokémon. A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

name: Zapdos
description: The Electric Pokémon. This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

name: Moltres
description: The Flame Pokémon. A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

name: Dratini
description: The Dragon Pokémon. Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon’s existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

name: Dragonair
description: The Dragon Pokémon. According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

name: Dragonite
description: The Dragon Pokémon. It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

name: Mewtwo
description: The Genetic Pokémon. Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

name: Mew
description: The New Species Pokémon. When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.
